						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone now used as door frame of the central shrine of the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jayasiṁha II—A.D. 1037-38.</p>						

						<p>The record is badly damaged, the ends of all the lines being mutilated. There are two dates, but both are incomplete (1) • • • • • <hi rend="bold">pushya, Amāvaśyā, eclipse. (2) • • • Īśvara, Saṁkrānti.</hi> The latter date, falling in the reign period of the king corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1037-38.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record contains the eulogy of a subordinate chief (name lost). It mentions Rēvaṇa-Bhaṭṭa and seems to record a gift of land on the latter date.</p>						

						</summary>
